    {
      "num": 1,
      "text": "According to the COSO Enterprise Risk Management Framework, which component specifically addresses the organization's risk appetite and risk tolerance levels?",
      "tag": "COSO Framework",
      "options": [
        "C. Performance",
        "D. Information, Communication, and Reporting",
        "B. Governance and Culture",
        "A. Strategy and Objective-Setting"
      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "The Strategy and Objective-Setting component explicitly establishes risk appetite during strategic planning and sets risk tolerances aligned with strategy. COSO ERM Framework (2017) identifies this as the foundational component where organizations define acceptable variation in outcomes relative to objectives, integrating risk considerations into business strategy and goal-setting processes.",
      "justification_wrong": "Other components support risk management but do not establish risk appetite. Governance and Culture sets tone and oversight; Performance involves identifying and assessing risks; Information and Communication supports decision-making. Only Strategy and Objective-Setting formally defines risk appetite and tolerance thresholds per COSO ERM guidelines.",
      "difficulty": "STANDARD",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "prevention_deterrence/quiz_001_en.json"
    },
    {
