      "justification_correct": "Strategy and Objective-Setting is where risk appetite is established and strategic alternatives are evaluated. COSO ERM 2017 emphasizes that fraud risks must be considered during strategic planning to prevent misalignment with organizational objectives, making this the primary component for early-stage fraud risk identification before operational deployment.",
      "justification_wrong": "While Performance monitoring, Communication, and Governance are essential ERM components, they operate reactively or supportively. Strategy and Objective-Setting proactively integrates fraud risk considerations into strategic decisions, preventing risks from embedding into operations. Other components address fraud risks after strategic direction is established, making them secondary.",
