      "options": [
        "B. Prioritize high-impact scenarios; apply proportionate controls based on risk severity",
        "A. Allocate controls equally across all risks regardless of impact",
        "C. Focus exclusively on low-impact, high-probability fraud only",
        "D. Defer all control improvements until external auditors recommend action"
      ],
      "correct": 0,
      "justification_correct": "Risk-based resource allocation is fundamental to fraud management. COSO and CFE standards mandate prioritizing high-impact scenarios with commensurate control investment. This maximizes protection of organizational assets and stakeholder interests.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option A wastes resources; C ignores material risk; D abdicates management responsibility. Effective fraud prevention requires proportionate investment aligned with impact severity, not uniform or deferred approaches.",
      "difficulty": "HARD",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "prevention_deterrence/quiz_003_en.json"
    },
    {
      "num": 10,
      "text": "Which of the following best reflects the relationship between the COSO framework's 'Monitoring' component and fraud risk management effectiveness?",
