        "C. Conduct fraud risk assessment → establish control environment → implement technology controls → train employees."
      ],
      "correct": 1,
      "justification_correct": "COSO Framework emphasizes control environment as foundational, followed by risk assessment, then control design and implementation, and finally monitoring. CFE Manual (Fraud Prevention) prescribes this sequence: tone at the top precedes all other elements, enabling effective risk identification and control design.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option B reverses sequence inappropriately; C separates assessment from environment improperly; D begins with controls prematurely. Effective fraud risk management requires foundational governance before risk assessment and control design—environment, assessment, controls, monitoring is the correct COSO-aligned hierarchy.",
